Class BELPin

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.BooleanFlagHelper
      • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.BELPin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class BELPin
extends BooleanFlagHelper
implements Serializable
    Represents a pin on an element, including a site port where this pin corresponds to a site pin. Created on: Oct 1, 2015

      • getSourcePin

        public BELPin getSourcePin()
        Examines all the BEL pins on the site wire and returns the first source (output pin). If this pin is an output, it returns itself (this). If no dedicated output pins are found, but the site wire has a bi-directional pin, it will return the bi-directional pin.
        Returns:
        The output pin on the attached site wire, or null if none could be found.
        Since:
        2019.2.1

      • getConnectedInputPinOnBEL

        public BELPin getConnectedInputPinOnBEL(BEL bel)
        Examines this pin and all pins connected on its site wire for an input pin on the provided BEL.
        Parameters:
        bel - The matching BEL of interested
        Returns:
        An input BELPin on the provided BEL that is connected to this BELPin or null if none was found.
        Since:
